                        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon"></span>
                    </a>
                </div>
			    	<div class="card-body">
			      		<p>On 2 October 2019, Marathon Race (7km) themed “RUN FOR PEACE” was organised by the Sports Board, Students Gymkhana Council,IIITG on the occasion of 150th Birth Anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi. In this event a total of 150 students (including 23 girls) and 15 volunteers were registered including Sports faculty coordinator and other faculty members. The event was started by Dr. Sounak Sir (Sports Coordinator ,IIITG), Mr. Mansoor Khan (Associate Sports Coordinator,IIITG) and Dr. Rakesh Biswas (Associate Sports Coordinator, IIITG) at 5:15 AM from the Academic Block IIITG to Kukurmara Substation (AEGCL) and then back again. Volunteers were assigned to distribute water and refreshments to runners at 3 various places. To make up with any medical emergency during the race a fully equipped ambulance with doctor followed the participants throughout the event.<br><br>

  						Students actively participated in the event and all managed to complete the race with flyers. To motivate the students we distributed medals ( sponsored by Gear Up and DP Enterprises )  to top 100 runners. And also the participants were provided Energy Drinks  at the end of the marathon. Overall, due to aforementioned event students as well as other faculty members of the institute got to know about the health benefits of running and being fit. Organising these kinds of event regularly will definitely help us to find the athletic talents in our institute and will increase awareness about being healthy and fit. The event ended at 7:30 AM  with the refreshments and success photographs with the finishers.</p>
			    	</div>
