			    	<div class="card-body">
			      		<p>To commemorate the 144th birth anniversary of Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel, on ‘Rashtriya Ekta Diwas’,  "Run for Unity" was organised in IIIT GUWAHATI with Sports Coordinator Dr. Sounak Roy flagging off the run. Dr. Roy paid tributes to the Iron man Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel followed by a Rastriya Ekta Unity Pledge and exhorted those present in the programme to work steadfastly for unity and integrity of the nation. Associate Sports Coordinator Dr. Md.Mansoor Khan and Dr. Rakesh Biswas also paid tribute to Patel Ji.<br><br>

						The event was started by Dr. Sounak Roy (Sports Coordinator ,IIITG), Dr. Mansoor Khan (Associate Sports Coordinator,IIITG) and Dr. Rakesh Biswas (Associate Sports Coordinator, IIITG) at 6:00 AM from the Academic Block,  IIITG to Boys Hostel and then back again. Volunteers were assigned to distribute water and refreshments to runners at different places. To make up with any medical emergency during the race a fully equipped ambulance with doctor followed the participants throughout the event.<br>

						Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel was a great leader of farmers, an administrator and always stood with the poor. His efforts in India’s unity and independence movement will always be remembered.</p>
