			    	<div class="card-body">
						<p>IIIT Guwahati’s Sports Board under Student Gymkhana Council (SGC) has been conducting various activities for physical, social, and psychological well-being of the students, faculty members, and staff members under the aegis of Fit India Movement. Based on the call of our Honourable Prime Minister, Fit India launched “Fit India Prabhat Pheri” advocating the message “फिटनेस का डोज़ – आधा घंटा रोज़” campaign in December 2020.IIIT GUWAHATI commemorates the “Fit India Movement" Campaign launched by the Hon’ble Prime Minister of India. Students were encouraged to participate in daily activities. Both Indoor and Outdoor sports are organised regularly. Proper training sessions are being conducted on a daily basis.<br><br>
						Prabhat Pheri is one of the ethnic Indian ways to promote a fit and healthy India. People in Indian villages have been taking part in early morning processions since ancient times chanting songs and using musical instruments. This activity aims to spread the benefits of fitness which will bring in a positive change in the local communities.<br>
						The Fit India Prabhat Pheri event is named as “Morning Energies” for IIITG that aims to encourage fitness and help all campus community to get freedom from obesity, laziness, stress, anxiety, diseases, etc. The event further aims in contributing the all over health care index of the country by taking necessary inputs from the Fitness-Club of IIITG (formed under Fit India Movement) concerning to the event.The fitness activities are monitored through the Fit India App and are advised to get installed in the participant’s smartphones. Participants can post their activity pictures and photographs on social media with #prabhatpheri_IIITG.</p>
